@startuml notification_state
!theme plain
title Notification State Chart Diagram

[*] --> Created

Created --> Pending : send()\n[Notification queued for delivery]

Pending --> Delivered : deliver()\n[Notification sent to user]

Delivered --> Read : markAsRead()\n[User reads notification]
Delivered --> Expired : expire()\n[Notification expires after timeout]

Read --> Archived : archive()\n[Notification moved to history]
Expired --> Archived : cleanup()\n[System cleanup process]

Archived --> [*] : delete()\n[Notification permanently removed]

' Error states
Pending --> Failed : deliveryFailed()\n[Delivery attempt failed]
Failed --> Pending : retry()\n[Retry delivery]
Failed --> Archived : giveUp()\n[Max retries exceeded]

' Self-transitions
Delivered --> Delivered : view()\n[User views notification again]
Read --> Read : reread()\n[User accesses read notification]

' Notes
note right of Created
  Notification created
  with user ID and message
end note

note right of Pending
  Queued for delivery
  to target user
end note

note right of Delivered
  Visible in user's
  notification panel
end note

note right of Read
  User has acknowledged
  the notification
end note

note right of Expired
  Notification timed out
  without being read
end note

note right of Failed
  Delivery failed
  (user offline, etc.)
end note

note right of Archived
  Stored in notification
  history for reference
end note

@enduml